    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm inclined to agree with @Carreau - I don't think this makes sense. Both technically and in terms of the interface - specifying a path to a virtualenv won't work when someone runs the notebook on another computer. Also, there are multiple efforts in this space (virtualenvs, conda, hashdist), and we should let them explore different approaches.\n\nYou might be interested in talking to @ahmadia, who is working on ideas for recreating an appropriate hashdist environment to run a notebook in.\n\nClosing for now, we can reopen if people disagree.\n"
  },
